EMPLOYMENT—DISPLACED PERSONS

Mr. Stewart (Winnipeg North):

1. How many displaced persons have completed their work contracts in Canada?

2. Is there any special employment policy for these people?

Mr. Cote (Verdun):

1. 6,629.

2. On completion of undertaking, displaced persons may accept employment of their own choosing in the same manner as other resi- dents. They are encouraged to remain in the employment to which they were assigned but are informed that the facilities of the national employment service are available to them it they wish to take other work. Local ofﬁces of the national employment service have been instructed to interview such applicants care- fully to ensure that the most suitable possible placements are made having regard to the applicants’ wishes and skills or trades possessed.
